    Fabric Retailers in Mumbai

    The Indian textile sector is growing at a staggering rate and is poised to scale greater heights. Most cities and towns have a dedicated market for textiles where citizens can purchase textile garments, un-stitched cloth, handloom materials and fabrics. With fabric retailers, you are bound to find a diverse range of fabrics, cloths and materials, several with rich embroidery, handiwork and embellishments. Owners of businesses source materials such as cotton, silk, polyester and linen in bulk from these retail shops. Walk into any fabric retail shop to discover a diverse assortment of fabrics that you can shop for stitching up a cushion cover for your favourite couch to designing a fabulous dress for your D-Day. These retailers may also offer tailoring services where you can get the fabric or material stitched as per your requirements. The price of the fabric depends on its type and varies from retailer to retailer. Find an extensive list of Fabric Retailers in Mumbai, on scrolling up the page.

    You can search Fabric Retailers in Mumbai on the basis of your location, popularity, ratings & reviews on Justdial.     Yes, several dealers stock such kind of party wear fabrics.

    2. Do fabric retailers in Mumbai stock fabrics from other parts of India?

    Yes, many retailers source fabrics from other parts of India such as Rajasthan, Gujarat and many other states.

    3. Do these retailers sell hand-woven fabrics?

    Many of them sell both silk and cotton hand-woven material with excellent colour options.

    4. Do they stock satin and velvety fabrics as well?

    Yes, a lot of them specialize in such fabrics.

    5. What is the cost of fabrics?

    The cost may vary from Rs. 35 to Rs. 150 per metre approximately.

    What is ICAI Endorsed?

    ICAI is a not for profit organisation

    The Electrical Safety program run by international Copper Association India (ICA India) since 2001 aims to educate and promote 'Safe Wiring Practices' to electricians and contractors across India. We conduct seminars, training programs and are also member of ET20 Committee of BIS (Bureau of Indian Standards) advocating improved wiring standards to encourage proper wiring and quality workmanship. The endorsed electrician / contractor has attended our seminar. This initiative is supported by ICAI Building Wire Program Partners(Anchor, Finolex, KEI, Polycab, RR Kabel & V Guard).
